article.headline: St. Bonaventure 60, Cent. Connecticut St. 57
article.story: NEW BRITAIN, Conn. (AP) -- Paul Williams had 16 points and 11 rebounds as St. Bonaventure blew a 15-point lead in the second half but held on for a 60-57 win over Central Connecticut State on Saturday. Central's Tristan Blackwood hit a 3-pointer as he was fouled and converted the free throw for a four-point play to put the Blue Devils (1-4) up 57-56 with 2:16 left in the game. St. Bonaventure (3-2) hit just five field goals in the second half, but Zarryon Fereti made four free throws in the final 13.5 seconds and Central failed to score on its last two possessions. Javier Mojica led Central with 25 points and 10 rebounds, and Blackwood finished with 15 points. The Blue Devils used a 17-4 run in the second half to turn a 15-point Bonnies' lead into a two-point game. Mojica's steal and coast-to-coast drive cut the lead to 48-45, and his 3-pointer pulled Central to within two at 50-48 with 8:43 to play. St. Bonaventure built its lead by taking control of the game late in the first half. The Bonnies took a 39-27 lead after a 9-0 run with 2:53 to go before intermission. A 3-pointer by Fereti put St. Bonaventure up 44-31 at halftime.
